    "extras": [
      "Argentina changes prices quickly, so lock in domestic flights and high-demand Patagonia hotels as early as possible.",
      "Carry some cash for smaller cafés, taxis, and tips, but use cards for bigger bookings to avoid exchange surprises.",
      "For Brazil-side Iguazu access, Indian travellers should verify current visa requirements before finalising the route.",
      "Vegetarian food is easiest in Buenos Aires and Mendoza; in Patagonia, look for pasta, risotto, soups, and café plates rather than classic parrillas.",
      "If you have fewer days, keep Buenos Aires, Iguazu Falls, Mendoza, and Patagonia as the core four and treat Salta plus Bariloche as add-ons.",
      "Use the Aerolíneas Argentinas Visit Argentina pass if available outside the country, because multiple flight legs are often cheaper when bundled."
